The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Berserk bull

 New Delhi, Oct. 8 (PTI): 

 The capitals cops went into a tizzy this morning after 

 a bull went berserk after it was reportedly shooed away 

 from Mahadev Road through which the Prime Minister and his 

 entourage was to pass.

 The bull run continued for over six hours through Connaught Place, Gole Market, the YMCA womens hostel and finally the MPs flats near Ram Manohar Lohia Hospital, where it was caught.

 The policemen, with the help of civic employees, tranquilised the animal that left six persons wounded. 




